(Format strings can build into buffers via set/append/copy)

a number called "n" is 42.
a buffer called "prefix" is "pre".
a buffer called "out" is "".

set out to "N={n:04}".
print out.

append " HEX={n:04X}" to out.
print out.

copy "BIN={n:b}" to out.
print out.

append " + tail" to out.
print out.

set out to "{prefix}-{n:03}-{n add 2}".
print out.
